{"parentUuid": null, "isSidechain": true, "promptId": "6c3a0b22-aa71-4abe-86b8-7ed7f2e35c75", "agentId": "a6dcd14d9aca72f9b", "type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "Adversarially verify this finding about a design doc (the doc is at /tmp/claude-1000/-home-jleechan-projects-worktree-runner/8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b/scratchpad/gistfile1.txt; the repo is /home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner; you may use WebSearch/WebFetch and read files). Try to REFUTE it. Finding from the \"rust\" reviewer, severity major:\nTITLE: sysinfo pulled in only to run System::new_all()+refresh_all() whose result is thrown away\nDETAIL: src/platform.rs lines 166\u2013167 create `let mut sys = System::new_all(); sys.refresh_all();` and then never read `sys` \u2014 the compiler will even warn about the unused variable. `System::new_all()` enumerates every process, CPU, and memory stat on the host (hundreds of syscalls / procfs reads) purely as dead weight in a function whose actual work is `cfg!`, `env::consts::ARCH`, a Path::exists, and a `which` lookup. OS detection needs no crate at all \u2014 `std::env::consts::OS` is free and compile-time-truthful.\nRECOMMENDATION: Two honest options: (a) drop sysinfo from Cargo.toml entirely for v1; or (b) actually use it \u2014 read total memory/CPU count to derive the resource limits that config.rs currently hardcodes (`memory: 4G, cpus: 2, count: 2` regardless of whether the host has 8 or 128 GB). Option (b) turns the dep from waste into the feature the tool claims to provide ('consistent resource protection everywhere'). If you keep it, use targeted refreshes (`System::new_with_specifics(RefreshKind::new().with_memory(...))`), never new_all.\nIs the finding factually correct and does the recommendation make sense? If the factual basis is wrong or the severity is inflated, refute it. Default to refuted=true only if you have concrete contrary evidence or the claim is unsupported after checking."}, "uuid": "10c537e2-fd28-4484-9c7f-b47dd29f7685", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T22:01:25.905Z", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner", "sessionId": "8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b", "version": "2.1.198", "gitBranch": "fix/linux-runner-pre-job-hook", "slug": "velvet-wishing-cake"}
